org.hibernate.sql.results.spi

Interface DomainResult<J>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ResultSetMappingNode
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BasicResultMappingNode<J>, DynamicInstantiationResult<R>, EntityResult

    public interface DomainResult<J>
extends ResultSetMappingNode
    Represents a result value in the domain query results. Acts as the producer for the DomainResultAssembler for this result as well as any Initializer instances needed

    Not the same as a result column in the JDBC ResultSet! This contract represents an individual domain-model-level query result. A QueryResult will usually consume multiple JDBC result columns.

    QueryResult is distinctly different from a Fetch and so modeled as completely separate hierarchy.

    See Also:
    BasicResultMappingNode, DynamicInstantiationResult, EntityResult, CollectionResult, CompositeResult, Fetch
